author: Maya Rostowska, VICE News
title: How Iceland Could Hold the Key to Understanding Coronavirus
description: Using its unique population data, a small genetics company is planning to screen 15,000 asymptomatic people to learn about the virus.
content: A small Icelandic genetics company made headlines in 2013 when it developed an app to prevent accidental incest in the insular country's dating scene. That was kind of a bust, but now the same company is using its genetics expertise to screen thousands of peo… [+1353 chars]
